di3rt.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr1di3rs/ded011c9-8397-45fd-98dc-b36839021a2b/d5a2b180-74e8-11f1-a0ae-9b2029c4e026/file-6y3zli1mr1di3rt.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>Two masses $M_1$ and $M_2$ are attached to the ends of a light string which passes over a massless pulley attached to the top of a double inclined smooth plane of angles of inclination $\\alpha$ and $\\beta$. If $M_2 > M_1$ and $\\beta > \\alpha$ then the acceleration of block $M_2$ down the inclined will be :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr1di3rs/ded011c9-8397-45fd-98dc-b36839021a2b/d5a2b180-74e8-11f1-a0ae-9b2029c4e026/file-6y3zli1mr1di3rt.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr1di3rs/ded011c9-8397-45fd-98dc-b36839021a2b/d5a2b180-74e8-11f1-a0ae-9b2029c4e026/file-6y3zli1mr1di3rt.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>$\\dfrac{M_2 g\\ (\\sin \\beta)}{M_1 + M_2}$</p>","<p>$\\dfrac{M_2 g\\ (\\sin \\alpha)}{M_1 + M_2}$</p>","<p>$\\left(\\dfrac{M_2 \\sin \\beta - M_1 \\sin \\alpha}{M_1 + M_2}\\right)g$</p>","<p>zero</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr1drk3w","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":3080673408,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>The pulley arrangements shown in figure are identical, the mass of the rope being negligible. In case I, the mass m is lifted by attaching a mass 2m to the other end of the rope.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr1du9nw/2b0997de-c2c9-42d0-9ac8-11a56e7e4a6d/27e58ac0-74ea-11f1-a0ae-9b2029c4e026/file-6y3zli1mr1du9nx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https: